I am thinking if we are moving to llvm-3.6 in the future, or we have multiple LLVM toolchains. We might test 3.6 like "make LLVM_PREBUILTS_PATH={where-3.6-bin} LLVM_PREBUILTS_HEADER_PATH={where-3.6-headers}".  

It is convenient if we could just set LLVM_PREBUILTS_PATH in the command line.  Could I know why "../"  is not recommended?

