As it stands, your change is extremely error-prone, so I am tempted to abandon it. If you intend for a developer to set both variables for 3.6, this change should be abandoned. If you actually want to make it work for changing out the version number (i.e. 3.5 -> 3.6), we need a different variable, as I suggested above. I am ok with either of those 2 options, but I am not ok with a relative path that still bakes in version-specific information.

